<chapter>
  <title><xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_FRA"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> Module</title>

  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml" xpointer="ent_FRA"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange Forward Rate Agreement (FRA) trades.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Forward Rate Agreements</title>

    <para role="TEXT">A Forward Rate Agreement (FRA) is a contract in which two parties
    agree to swap a floating rate for a predetermined rate on a notional
    deposit of specified maturity at a specified future time (the settlement
    date). The contract period for a FRA is quoted as, for example, 3 X 6,
    meaning the interest rate for a three-month period commencing three months
    from now.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">The "buyer" of an FRA wishes to be protected against a rise in
    interest rates on a deposit to be received at a future time; the "seller"
    wishes to be protected against interest rate decline on a loan to be made
    for future delivery. If the floating index rate on the settlement date is
    higher than the agreed rate, the buyer receives payment of the difference
    from the seller; if the floating index rate is lower than the agreed rate,
    the seller receives payment.</para>

    <para role="TEXT">An average FRA is defined as an FRA whose fixing rate is derived as
    an average of rates observed during a specified period that is different
    from the payment period.</para>
  </section>

